# Standalone SPURIOUS_DATA → decoder code 0x2001 (L2-DEC-020).
#
# A SPURIOUS_DATA (type 0x20) record that is NOT preceded by an errored record
# is classified 0x2001 (standalone), as opposed to 0x2000 (continuation of a
# preceding error — the case exercised by errors-inline.hex). Here a clean
# NORMAL record precedes the spurious record, so `prev_was_error` is false and
# the standalone 0x2001 branch is taken.

# Record 1: normal RT15 SA11 Receive (byte-identical to count-one.hex). A clean,
# non-errored prior record so the following spurious record is standalone.
02240F1826DB21F6
7E79
0004 0000 0000 2F00 22CA 2F00 22CA
0000 0000 0000 0000 0000 0000 0000 0000
0000 0000 0000 0000 0000 0000 0000 0000
0000 0000 0000 0000 0000 0000
71C7 0078

# Record 2: SPURIOUS_DATA with two raw words, no preceding error → code 0x2001.
# TW 0x0620 (type=0x20, wc=6) + IRIG (0x180F, 0xDB26, 0xF738) + raw AAAA BBBB.
2006 0F18 26DB 38F7
AAAA BBBB

# end-of-records terminator
0000
